<text>Queen Anne&#x27;s lace is a common name for a number of plants in the family Apiaceae.
including:
* &quot;Ammi majus&quot;, native in the Nile River Valley
* &quot;Anthriscus sylvestris&quot;, a herbaceous biennial or short-lived perennial plant
* &quot;Daucus carota&quot;, native to temperate Eurasia and naturalized in Australia and North America; the wild form of the domesticated carrot</text><links>
